This article describes update the microcode of AMD processors.

== Installation ==

=== Firmware ===
Install {{Package|sys-firmware/amd-ucode}}:
{{Emerge|amd-ucode}}

{{Note|Because Dresden, Germany based Operating System Research Center team out of business, please download from: http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/repo/pkgs/microcode_ctl/amd-ucode-2012-09-10.tar/559bc355d3799538584add80df2996f0/amd-ucode-2012-09-10.tar}}

=== Kernel ===
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
Processor type and features  --->
    [*] /dev/cpu/microcode - microcode support
    [ ]   Intel microcode patch loading support
    [*]   AMD microcode patch loading support

Device Drivers  --->
    Generic Driver Options 
        (amd-ucode/microcode_amd.bin amd-ucode/microcode_amd_fam15h.bin) External firmware blobs to build into the kernel binary
</pre>}}

You can now reboot computer. Module microcode should autoload and update microcode of CPU from firmware directory.

